<HL>
   International Brief -- Rothmans International PLC:
   Firm Will Buy Dutch Unit
   Of American Brands Inc.
</HL>
<DATE>
07/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   U.RIN AMB
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
TOBACCO PRODUCTS (TOB)
</IN>
<LP>
   Rothmans International PLC, London, said Monday that it
has agreed to buy the Dutch tobacco unit of American Brands
Inc. for 245 million guilders ($131 million).
   The purchase of Theodorus Niemeyer B.V., a unit of
American Brands's Gallaher Ltd. subsidiary, is aimed at
strengthening Rothmans's position in the pipe and fine-cut
tobacco markets in continental Europe, the company said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Gallaher will continue to market the Dutch company's
Saamson, Can and Holland House tobaccos in the U.K. and
Ireland.
   Niemeyer is expected to show net assets of 172 million
guilders as of June 30. For the nine months ended June 30,
pretax profit is estimated to have been 34 million guilders.
   American Brands is based in Old Greenwich, Conn.
</TEXT>
